The Mountain

At the hill's board, prone,
While nature faces down,
We behold ten feet in eyes,
Yet from one roofâ€”the fall.
Beneath forth hold what can speak,
Blood is known in the soil,
And all the shade and boughs.
Straight looked our dead on me.

 - Ralph Waldo Emerson

